 Hi folks! <br>
<br>
I play a lvl 35 norseman skald named Homeslice on the Kay server with Augmented Dexterity 2 and Mastery of Pain 1. This is my first and only character. <br>
<br>
I know that there are several posts concerning the issues I have questions about, but they're all just a bit too techincal for me. And so, any answers that you give please go into a bit of detail and remember that I'm a n00b gimp!  <br>
<br>
So, with all of that said, I have a few questions: <br>
<br>
1. What is the the most effective way to spec myself?<br>
<br>
*Depends on what you plan on doing.  Here's the general guid that will ensure you are not gimped:<br>
<br>
MIN: 39 Weapon skill (only missing 2 styles)<br>
MIN: 43 Battlesong (last runspeed, but missing last damage add and last DD)<br>
<br>
Some common templates are:<br>
            R6 and mastery of parry 1 with full items bonus<br>
W:44&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 63<br>
S: 46&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 65<br>
P: 17&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 42&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
W:50&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 69<br>
S:43&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 62<br>
P:2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 27<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
W:47&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 66<br>
S:46&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 65<br>
P: 5&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 30<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
W:39&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 58<br>
S:46&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 65<br>
P:26&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 51<br>
<br>
Note 3 things.  Some like parry, some do not.  If you don't like parry, then your next decision is do you want all the good RvR battlesongs, or do you want Axe with Tyr's Fury.  The best of all worlds IMO is 44/46/17, either Axe or Hammer.  We have skalds that use each of the templates above, and all are veterans in RvR and do fine, and like their spec.  So just pick one and go with it.<br>
<br>
2. Axe, sword, or hammer? Which is the overall best?<br>
<br>
Hammer: Good vs assassins, albion tanks, some support classes.  Good styles, great RvR style, provoke, uses 1/2 the end of most othe anytime styles and does good damage (med defense penalty though, not good for duels)<br>
<br>
AXE:  Good styles, higher end than hammer (provoke), great level 50 style, but is 2nd in a chain off a front positional style.  Good vs scale wearing hibs (a lot of hibs), and better than hammer on clerics/minstrels, but worse on plate tanks.<br>
<br>
Both have a nice 2 chain rear style.  Axe has a great side positional style.  Most popular right now is Axe spec over hammer.  HIbs rarely play on my server, so hammer is still my choice.  ON a hib dominant server, Id strongly suggest Axe.<br>
<br>
Swords: Most SKalds respec out of swords for whatever reason.<br>
<br>
3. 1-handed or 2-handed?<br>
2H, for PvE and RvR.  Keep a 1H in RvR just for blade turn, otherwise, all 2H.<br>
<br>
4. Which realm abilities should I get? <br>
<br>
Here's some you can't go wrong with:<br>
<br>
IP/FA2 (you must get this..get it first)<br>
Purge (unless you ALWAYS group with a healer..even then it's still useful)<br>
aug dex 2<br>
Mastery of pain II<br>
Mastery of Parry I (worth it if you get pain II)<br>
Tough1<br>
AvoidanceOfMagic 1<br>
LongWind 1<br>
<br>
That's R5L5<br>
<br>
<br>
***FOr PVE RA's<br>
I'd get MCL first, then tireless for faster end regen sitting, and mastery of parry 1 or 2.  <br>
I like MCL over potions, but you can use potions for power boost if you like.  You can respec out of them once you get close to 50 and want to RvR full time. (I kept them all and still prefer them..even at Rank6+<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
<br>
-Dane<br>
